+{"id":"frankenpandas-6nexq","title":"fd90.155: add prelude_completeness unit test covering fd90.121-144 additions","description":"fd90.74-154 follow-on. The prelude expansion across fd90.121-fd90.144 added many items but the existing prelude tests (prelude_smoke_test, prelude_query_works, prelude_io_roundtrip, prelude_concat_works, prelude_to_datetime_works) only exercise the OLD prelude surface. Items added by recent work — nan* primitives, MergeExecutionOptions, MergeValidateMode, AsofDirection, DuplicateKeep, ConcatJoin, DropNaHow, MergedDataFrame, GroupByError, TypeError, JoinError, etc. — aren't exercised by any test.\n\nA user accidentally removing one of these from the prelude wouldn't surface a test failure until the integration tests added in fd90.146 happened to depend on it.\n\nFix: add a 'prelude_completeness' unit test inside crates/frankenpandas/src/lib.rs that does a no-op let-binding through each NEW prelude item (everything added since fd90.121). This is purely a compile-time guard — if any item gets removed from the prelude, the test refuses to compile.\n\nVerify with cargo test -p frankenpandas --lib. Pure additive test.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"test","created_at":"2026-04-26T15:03:15.197547410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T15:06:53.923880880Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T15:06:53.921238537Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
